THE GAME
--------

  'TriOtix' is a Workbench game played on a triangular shaped
board. The idea is to move a coloured bar from the highest
position, to the exit at the lower position, where a small square
is located. The game board is filled with 24 bars, including the
coloured bar, each occupying two spaces. An empty space, indicated
by a small dot, is placed somewhere on the game board.

  To move a bar, it must be beside the empty space. Clicking on
part of a bar which is next to the empty space will make the bar
rotate towards the empty space.

  One thing to keep in mind is that the 'figure 8' shaped bars can
rotate and can be placed in any position, even diagonally.
However, the coloured bar can only be placed horizontally or
vertically...

  When a portion of the coloured bar is placed on the exit at the
bottom of the game board, the game is completed... Complete the
game in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

